CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 14, 1959, pg. 19 reads: "Winter Meeting - Members of the Tommy Smith All-Star softball team met at the Flamingo Hotel last week to discuss plans for the coming softball season.  The team is champion of the Ammon Slow Pitch League.  Left to right, front row: Bill Johnson, Gabe Patterson, manager; George Penix, secretary; Tommy Smith, team sponsor; Robert Wooden, assistant manager, and Frank (Pretty Boy) Stotts.  Back row: Charlie Hull, Harry Holt, Jim Weaver, Joe Dogan and Wendell Austin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Tommy Smith All-Star softball team members, front row from left: Bill Johnson, Gabe Patterson, George Penix, sponsor Tommy Smith, Robert Wooden, Frank "Pretty Boy" Stotts; back row: Charlie Hull, Harry Holt, Jim Weaver, Joe Dogan, and Wendell Austin, gathered in Flamingo Hotel
